1
00:00:01,710 --> 00:00:04,210
She took the bait. Let's move.

2
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:14,290
She took the bait?

3
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:16,320
Yes.

4
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:19,960
Noon, during lunch, at the spot.
You know the one, right?

5
00:00:22,430 --> 00:00:24,760
"Noon, during lunch, at that spot?"

6
00:00:25,430 --> 00:00:27,270
What are they up to? A secret rendezvous?

7
00:00:28,300 --> 00:00:30,640
If they're meeting secretly
during their lunch break,

8
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,840
they must be dating.

9
00:00:36,010 --> 00:00:37,640
This is just too good.

10
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,880
- Are you two dating?
- Goodness!

11
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:46,220
I'm the one pestering Baek Ho.
You got a problem with that?

12
00:00:48,150 --> 00:00:49,150
Shit!

13
00:00:49,420 --> 00:00:52,690
Wash these.
That's what you get for scaring me.

14
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:02,500
Goodness!

15
00:01:03,700 --> 00:01:06,670
Mom, if you need more veggies,
get some more from the self-serve bar.

16
00:01:07,370 --> 00:01:09,810
But why has Tae Pyung been so busy lately?

17
00:01:09,870 --> 00:01:11,980
It's been a while
since he's even eaten at our place.

18
00:01:12,240 --> 00:01:14,850
Tae Pyung is busy. He's going to Thailand.

19
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:17,450
Thailand? Mom, did you just say Thailand?

20
00:01:17,650 --> 00:01:20,350
Uncle said he was going to Thailand.

21
00:01:21,150 --> 00:01:24,960
Just because he made a little money,
he's going to blow it all?

22
00:01:25,090 --> 00:01:27,190
Does he think all the profits are his
because the restaurant's doing well?

23
00:01:36,100 --> 00:01:37,800
San Wol, have you been waiting long?

24
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,940
- James Park will be here any minute.
- Will he?

25
00:01:41,010 --> 00:01:42,810
He's Korean-American,

26
00:01:42,810 --> 00:01:44,540
so his Korean is poor.
Please bear with him.

27
00:01:44,810 --> 00:01:46,880
- I see.
- So, about the stocks?

28
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:48,780
Of course. I have them right here.

29
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,220
I just need to sign them over, right?

30
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,750
Exactly.

31
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:55,320
You brought a big bag for the cash, right?

32
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:57,790
Please, why would I need a bag?

33
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,020
He can just wire the money to my account,

34
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:03,830
and I can invest it directly
into that AI crypto.

35
00:02:05,060 --> 00:02:07,300
Right. As you'll see
when you meet him, San Wol,

36
00:02:07,370 --> 00:02:09,730
he wasn't always this rich.

37
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,540
But he bought this crypto,

38
00:02:11,540 --> 00:02:13,570
and suddenly,
he could afford a building in Gangnam.

39
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,640
Oh my gosh.

40
00:02:14,970 --> 00:02:16,010
I'm so jealous.

41
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:19,840
I think that's him now.

42
00:02:42,970 --> 00:02:45,900
- Hi, Tae Pyung.
- James Park!

43
00:02:47,010 --> 00:02:48,910
- What's up?
- What's up, man?

44
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,280
I'm sorry.

45
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:58,650
- Nice to meet you.
- Right...

46
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:03,620
Hello.

47
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,260
I'm...

48
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,530
James Park.

49
00:03:07,830 --> 00:03:10,800
Yes, I'm Yeom San Wol.

50
00:03:13,030 --> 00:03:16,400
This is who I am.

51
00:03:27,450 --> 00:03:29,780
Baek Ho, you set up the virtual account,
right?

52
00:03:30,780 --> 00:03:32,550
I'm sending you the funds now,

53
00:03:32,950 --> 00:03:34,550
so use them to buy Yeom San Wol's shares.

54
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:35,790
Okay?

55
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:39,260
Okay. That's okay, yes.

56
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:43,960
You're so pretty.

57
00:03:44,100 --> 00:03:45,300
Are you single?

58
00:03:45,630 --> 00:03:46,730
What was it again?

59
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:49,530
- Not married...
- Miss?

60
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:52,970
- Oh, yes. Miss?
- Oh my, "miss"?

61
00:03:53,710 --> 00:03:54,810
She's not a "miss."

62
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,680
Anyway, this is San Wol,
the woman I told you about.

63
00:03:58,780 --> 00:04:00,210
And you, James Park,

64
00:04:00,850 --> 00:04:03,180
are very handsome.

65
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:05,020
- A handsome guy!
- Thank you.

66
00:04:05,420 --> 00:04:07,750
James, your business card is pretty slick.

67
00:04:08,490 --> 00:04:11,520
It’s not exactly my perfect dream setup,

68
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,160
but I’ve got two handsome guys
in front of me.

69
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:17,630
I should take a picture to remember this.

70
00:04:18,730 --> 00:04:20,870
- What?
- No, I mean,

71
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,870
I'm just so happy right now...

72
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:26,140
that I want to burn it into my memory.

73
00:04:28,010 --> 00:04:32,680
But you look really familiar.

74
00:04:38,280 --> 00:04:40,650
Yes! That's right, baby.

75
00:04:40,850 --> 00:04:42,750
I have a memorable face.

76
00:04:42,890 --> 00:04:44,860
I get that a lot.

77
00:04:45,690 --> 00:04:48,360
A Korean actor? Like Won Bin?

78
00:04:48,590 --> 00:04:49,830
Like Jung Woo Sung?

79
00:04:49,830 --> 00:04:51,660
Like Go Soo? That's it.

80
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:57,200
San Wol, are you eyeing another guy
when I'm right here?

81
00:04:57,340 --> 00:04:58,400
No, it's not like that.

82
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:02,310
Look at Tae Pyung getting all jealous.

83
00:05:03,470 --> 00:05:06,080
Let's get down to business.
We don't have a lot of time.

84
00:05:06,140 --> 00:05:07,210
Right. Of course.

85
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:08,880
Okay.

86
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:11,950
I am a CEO.

87
00:05:12,450 --> 00:05:15,350
Coin investment company.

88
00:05:15,420 --> 00:05:17,920
So, Dream stock,

89
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:20,290
balance trading...

90
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:21,660
The balance, right?

91
00:05:22,260 --> 00:05:24,960
- OTC trading.
- Anyway,

92
00:05:25,830 --> 00:05:28,200
I'm here because you said you'd sell.

93
00:05:28,530 --> 00:05:30,670
Yes. Okay.

94
00:05:32,900 --> 00:05:33,940
Ten times.

95
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:35,710
Ten.

96
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:39,010
- Is that right?
- You don't trust me?

97
00:05:39,780 --> 00:05:42,210
I'm really offended. I'm going home.

98
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:44,850
I'm a very busy man. You know that!

99
00:05:46,020 --> 00:05:48,590
Of course I know. Calm down.

100
00:05:48,790 --> 00:05:49,790
Don't...

101
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:51,860
You can't just leave.

102
00:05:53,490 --> 00:05:54,890
You can sign here.

103
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:57,100
Sign here now.

104
00:05:57,300 --> 00:05:58,500
If you don't, I'm going home.

105
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:02,100
Sign...

106
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,740
(Stock Transfer Agreement)

107
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:14,080
- The stamp.
- The stamp? Both of them?

108
00:06:14,150 --> 00:06:15,150
Both...

109
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:27,790
(Yeom San Wol)

110
00:06:31,860 --> 00:06:33,900
Baek Ho. Tae Pyung.

111
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,670
Now, just take Yeom San Wol
to a nearby brokerage firm,

112
00:06:37,140 --> 00:06:39,470
and it's over once we get that
one percent of Dream stock.

113
00:06:42,070 --> 00:06:43,470
We're almost there.

114
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:46,980
What? Were you hiding here?

115
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,790
Are you here alone, Director Ma?

116
00:06:56,920 --> 00:06:58,490
It sounded like you were talking
to someone.

117
00:06:58,860 --> 00:07:00,320
Are you that obsessed with me?

118
00:07:00,320 --> 00:07:01,860
Do you just follow me around all day?

119
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:03,590
Following you? As if.

120
00:07:07,370 --> 00:07:08,900
Why are you all up in my face?

121
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:10,770
Ma Seo Rin.

122
00:07:12,270 --> 00:07:14,210
Since when do you wear glasses?

123
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:19,080
Shit! My eyes felt a bit dry,
so I put them on.

124
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:21,810
Do I have to report
every little thing I do to you?

125
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:27,190
By the way, weren't you supposed
to meet Baek Ho at noon?

126
00:07:27,590 --> 00:07:29,090
What, are you mocking me?

127
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:32,960
As if Jun Ho rejecting me wasn't enough,
Baek Ho blew me off too. I'm a wreck.

128
00:07:34,090 --> 00:07:35,530
Being pissed off is making me hungry.

129
00:07:36,030 --> 00:07:38,300
Go out and get me some
Dubai chewy cookies.

130
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,160
Why me?

131
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:42,000
Because you're the one who made me mad.

132
00:07:43,230 --> 00:07:44,670
Our lunch break is almost over.

133
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:47,170
Hurry up and go get it.
What if they sell out?

134
00:07:50,210 --> 00:07:52,510
(Haneum Stock)

135
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:53,740
Ms. Yeom.

136
00:07:54,510 --> 00:07:57,450
I did the wire transfer.

137
00:07:57,780 --> 00:07:59,350
- Did you check?
- Oh my.

138
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:05,220
(Transaction History:
James Park, 17.19 million dollars)

139
00:08:09,790 --> 00:08:13,530
It's here. The money's here.
The deposit's been confirmed.

140
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:17,870
And I got the Dream Hotel stock.

141
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:19,700
One percent, thank you.

142
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,740
I should be thanking you.

143
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:26,280
Tae Pyung.
Now for the most important part.

144
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:29,210
Of course. We should both be thankful.

145
00:08:29,850 --> 00:08:32,450
Should we just forget
about the crypto investment?

146
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:33,820
What are you talking about?

147
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:36,750
After all we went through
to get this money?

148
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:40,390
You were going to let me experience
the joy of a tenfold return,

149
00:08:40,460 --> 00:08:41,760
and you made time for this.

150
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,130
How can you suggest we quit?

151
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:46,760
Yes! Money is like a snowball.

152
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:48,270
You know what I mean, right?

153
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:50,270
- A snowball.
- Yes, right.

154
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:52,440
You roll it, and it gets bigger.

155
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:55,840
- I see.
- It starts off small,

156
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,610
and then it gets bigger and bigger.

157
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:01,150
Wait.

158
00:09:01,250 --> 00:09:03,950
I need to invest right away
to make ten times my money, right?

159
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:07,220
- You want to do it right now?
- Yes.

160
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:09,990
(Buy Order Submitted,
Buy Order Completed Successfully)

161
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:13,160
Ms. Yeom, you're amazing.

162
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:15,790
- Wait, are you putting it all in?
- Yes.

163
00:09:15,790 --> 00:09:17,730
I can't be held responsible for this.

164
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:19,760
Gosh.

165
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:21,800
It's done, right?

166
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,170
- What?
- It's done.

167
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:24,270
The order came in.

168
00:09:24,270 --> 00:09:25,300
Okay?

169
00:09:26,070 --> 00:09:27,070
Yes.

170
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:32,610
I'll make it worth your while later
for setting this up.

171
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,280
Let's take a trip
to Hong Kong later, okay?

172
00:09:37,210 --> 00:09:39,650
Yes, of course, Hong Kong sounds nice.

173
00:09:41,450 --> 00:09:42,620
Maybe we should go to Hawaii too.

174
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:46,790
Hey, James.
How about going to Hawaii together?

175
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:48,730
How about the three of us go together?

176
00:09:48,860 --> 00:09:51,200
Of course. Yes!

177
00:09:55,570 --> 00:09:59,540
Tae Pyung, I'm going to head out.
I'll see you later.

178
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,840
Take care.

179
00:10:02,210 --> 00:10:03,210
Bye.

180
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:10,610
Yes.

181
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,520
Unbelievable.

182
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:23,390
So with this, one percent
of Yeom San Wol's shares...

183
00:10:24,030 --> 00:10:25,160
is ours now, right?

184
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,930
Jang Mi, we did it.

185
00:10:31,470 --> 00:10:32,840
Where did you get these?

186
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:35,270
Gosh.

187
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,980
Let go of me.

188
00:10:38,980 --> 00:10:41,150
Let go! That really hurts!

189
00:10:41,610 --> 00:10:45,180
- It's supposed to hurt. That's the point.
- Exactly.

190
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,750
Inmate 6620, you have a visitor.

191
00:10:54,090 --> 00:10:55,360
You monsters.

192
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:57,400
Just wait till I get out of here.

193
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:01,830
I'll hunt every single one of you down
and rip you to shreds.

194
00:11:06,470 --> 00:11:09,210
(Visiting Schedule)

195
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:29,830
Look at the state of your face.

196
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,000
Why are you just letting them hit you?

197
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,430
Just like you did to me,

198
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:38,640
you should've slapped them.

199
00:11:39,800 --> 00:11:42,510
If you couldn't overpower them,
you should've at least bitten them.

200
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:45,580
You have to do whatever it takes
to protect yourself.

201
00:11:47,450 --> 00:11:48,650
You've always been a fighter.

202
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:53,020
So what's with this pathetic state
you're in now?

203
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:54,750
Jun Ho.

204
00:11:55,220 --> 00:11:57,190
You abandoned me, just to live like this?

205
00:11:59,560 --> 00:12:01,760
So I could see you in this pathetic state?

206
00:12:05,500 --> 00:12:06,930
Jun Ho, don't go! Jun Ho!

207
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:09,430
Let me see your face, Jun Ho.

208
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:12,570
Please? My son, Jun Ho.

209
00:12:23,780 --> 00:12:25,650
When I went so long without seeing you,

210
00:12:26,180 --> 00:12:27,380
I just got by.

211
00:12:28,590 --> 00:12:32,190
But now, not being able to see you
is driving me crazy.

212
00:12:33,590 --> 00:12:36,690
It felt like I was
going through withdrawal.

213
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:39,300
I missed you that much.

214
00:12:43,300 --> 00:12:46,370
- I mean it, Jun Ho.
- Then why'd you do it? Why?

215
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:49,640
You're mistaken. I'm not the killer.

216
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,080
I've seen the video evidence.

217
00:12:52,410 --> 00:12:54,310
And what about
the late Oh Bok Gil's cell phone?

218
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,550
I heard you were the one who had it.

219
00:12:57,380 --> 00:12:59,180
Isn't that clear evidence?

220
00:13:00,680 --> 00:13:03,920
It was a setup.
I'm telling you, it wasn't me.

221
00:13:04,460 --> 00:13:05,660
So please...

222
00:13:06,060 --> 00:13:07,390
Listen to me,

223
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:09,260
and just believe me.

224
00:13:09,930 --> 00:13:11,260
You don't really think your own mother...

225
00:13:11,860 --> 00:13:14,100
could be such a monster, do you, Jun Ho?

226
00:13:17,670 --> 00:13:19,070
I'll be getting out of here soon.

227
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:21,710
As soon as I'm cleared of these charges,
I can get out.

228
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:25,240
Is that true?

229
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:27,140
This whole thing was a setup.

230
00:13:27,810 --> 00:13:30,950
You know if someone wants to frame you,
they can make up anything.

231
00:13:31,450 --> 00:13:33,680
You're old enough to have seen
that much of the world, aren't you?

232
00:13:34,820 --> 00:13:37,520
So don't fall for it.

233
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:39,720
Just trust me and wait.

234
00:13:39,920 --> 00:13:41,160
Okay, Jun Ho?

235
00:13:42,230 --> 00:13:44,700
Who would dare try to frame you?

236
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:49,830
You wouldn't understand
even if I told you right now.

237
00:13:50,630 --> 00:13:53,800
In business, you make so many enemies.

238
00:13:59,110 --> 00:14:00,110
Is the food...

239
00:14:02,550 --> 00:14:03,580
edible?

240
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:07,750
When I get out...

241
00:14:13,220 --> 00:14:17,360
Once I get out of here,
I'd like to have a meal with you.

242
00:14:18,630 --> 00:14:21,030
Would you do that for me, Jun Ho?

243
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:23,570
What makes you think
I'd want to eat with you?

244
00:14:28,740 --> 00:14:29,740
Jun Ho.

245
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:32,340
Just focus on getting out of here
in one piece.

246
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:36,810
I will. I'll get out of here, you hear me?

247
00:14:36,810 --> 00:14:38,120
I swear I will.

248
00:14:50,390 --> 00:14:51,600
You know what?

249
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:55,070
I think we need to get
CEO Chae out of there.

250
00:14:55,730 --> 00:14:56,800
Yes, Chairman.

251
00:14:56,930 --> 00:14:58,740
Love her or hate her,

252
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,910
she's still the mother of my child,
Seo Rin.

253
00:15:03,140 --> 00:15:05,780
And I can't have my daughter living
as the daughter of a murderer.

254
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:08,110
And we have to marry her off, you know.

255
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,080
For Director Ma's sake, you're right, sir.

256
00:15:11,350 --> 00:15:14,590
Okay, right now,
send one of those boxes...

257
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:17,120
to Minister Kim...

258
00:15:18,190 --> 00:15:20,090
and tell him to arrange for
CEO Chae's release.

259
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,230
Tell him if he does this for me,
I'll be sure to return the favor.

260
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:27,330
How's Mom doing?

261
00:15:27,670 --> 00:15:31,770
Yes. She still asks for you, Jang Mi,
but not as much as she used to.

262
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:36,640
Here.

263
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,040
Use this for household expenses.

264
00:15:39,340 --> 00:15:42,980
And please tell Mom that
I love her very much.

265
00:15:43,110 --> 00:15:45,350
Hey, this is way too much.

266
00:15:45,420 --> 00:15:49,050
I feel guilty leaving you and our sister
to take care of Mom.

267
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:52,160
What are you talking about?
We know how hard you have it.

268
00:15:54,090 --> 00:15:56,790
Anyway, call me if anything comes up.

269
00:15:57,530 --> 00:15:58,530
I will.

270
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:01,670
Bye.

271
00:16:11,010 --> 00:16:12,910
- Did Tae Pyung already leave?
- Goodness."

272
00:16:14,110 --> 00:16:15,110
Yes.

273
00:16:16,210 --> 00:16:19,950
Baek Ho, I heard your accent was spot-on.
Too bad I missed it.

274
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:23,250
- Really? Was I cool?
- You totally pulled it off.

275
00:16:23,550 --> 00:16:25,320
You seem to have a knack for acting.

276
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:31,500
I'm sure Baek Ho
and Director Ma are together.

277
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:34,370
What are you talking about?
Why would those two be together?

278
00:16:34,970 --> 00:16:36,400
I heard it with my own two ears.

279
00:16:36,900 --> 00:16:39,800
She was like,
"Yes. Noon, during lunch, at that spot."

280
00:16:40,340 --> 00:16:42,670
"You know the one, right?"

281
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:44,710
Just like a couple on a secret date.

282
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:46,310
Can you believe that?

283
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:51,380
All right, I'll contact Baek Ho.
You can go back to your desk now.

284
00:16:52,380 --> 00:16:53,450
I'm counting on you.

285
00:16:54,690 --> 00:16:59,260
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

286
00:17:09,970 --> 00:17:11,440
Hey, Jun Ho, what's up?

287
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,040
Are you with Director Ma?

288
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:15,910
No. Why?

289
00:17:16,710 --> 00:17:19,540
- Isn't Seo Rin at her desk?
- What do you mean, "Seo Rin?"

290
00:17:20,380 --> 00:17:21,880
She's going to be your sister-in-law.

291
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,520
- Watch your mouth.
- Hey, what's the matter?

292
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:28,320
What's all this "sister-in-law" talk?
Don't get ahead of yourself.

293
00:17:28,420 --> 00:17:29,420
Listen.

294
00:17:29,690 --> 00:17:32,920
Why would you go around telling people
you're meeting Director Ma at noon?

295
00:17:33,220 --> 00:17:34,760
The staff could hear you
and get the wrong idea.

296
00:17:35,060 --> 00:17:36,360
Why are you being so reckless?

297
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:38,160
You're being so sensitive.

298
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:39,860
Are you...

299
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:42,830
cheating on Jang Mi behind her back?

300
00:17:43,770 --> 00:17:46,300
I'm asking if you're two-timing her.
Why can't you answer me?

301
00:17:46,370 --> 00:17:49,340
Two-timing?
Jang Mi is the only one for me.

302
00:17:49,610 --> 00:17:51,940
Besides, people can meet for work.

303
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:53,510
Do I have to report every little thing
I do to you?

304
00:17:53,610 --> 00:17:54,980
That's not what I'm talking about.

305
00:17:55,310 --> 00:17:57,680
I told you to stay away from Director Ma,
didn't I?

306
00:17:57,820 --> 00:17:59,350
Just because you tell me not to,

307
00:17:59,350 --> 00:18:01,150
I'm supposed to say, "Yes, sir"?

308
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:04,250
I do what I want.
It's not your place to tell me what to do.

309
00:18:04,350 --> 00:18:07,420
We shouldn't discuss this over the phone.
Let's talk later.

310
00:18:12,460 --> 00:18:13,460
Kang Baek Ho.

311
00:18:14,060 --> 00:18:17,000
After all that talk about
how much you like that Oh Jang Mi woman,

312
00:18:19,000 --> 00:18:20,840
now you're trying to have your cake
and eat it too?

313
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:26,810
Baek Ho.

314
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:29,680
There's no point in provoking
General Manager Kang.

315
00:18:29,780 --> 00:18:33,280
So you want me not to see you
just because he said to?

316
00:18:33,450 --> 00:18:34,720
Is that what you want?

317
00:18:34,720 --> 00:18:36,950
No, that's not what I mean.

318
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:40,220
But Jun Ho's only acting that way
because he doesn't know I'm Oh Jang Mi.

319
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:43,430
Still.
I can't say one thing and do another.

320
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:47,700
Anyway,
I appreciate you standing up for me.

321
00:18:48,670 --> 00:18:51,870
Anyway, I have to come clean
about being Oh Jang Mi.

322
00:18:52,170 --> 00:18:54,400
Deceiving everyone like this
has me on pins and needles.

323
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:58,310
Right. Now that we've had
Chae Hwa Young arrested,

324
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:00,480
and we've really stuck it to
Yeom San Wol...

325
00:19:01,810 --> 00:19:02,850
Right.

326
00:19:04,410 --> 00:19:06,420
(Commissary deposit information)

327
00:19:09,090 --> 00:19:10,120
Gosh.

328
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:18,660
Hey.

329
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:21,060
Have you ever done laundry in your life?

330
00:19:21,800 --> 00:19:24,330
Why would you hang it up
all wrinkled like that?

331
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:27,700
As if she's ever done laundry
with her own two hands.

332
00:19:29,110 --> 00:19:30,140
Hey, you witch.

333
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:33,080
- Can't you do anything right?
- Seriously.

334
00:19:33,140 --> 00:19:35,580
She only learns her lesson
after a good beating.

335
00:19:35,650 --> 00:19:37,250
- We have to teach her another lesson.
- Yes.

336
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:40,020
Wait, stop!

337
00:19:43,050 --> 00:19:45,290
Wait, just hear me out.

338
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,860
Once I get out of here,

339
00:19:48,490 --> 00:19:50,490
I'll give all of you jobs at my hotel.

340
00:19:51,430 --> 00:19:54,100
I guarantee you'll all have jobs.

341
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:57,570
- Let's make a deal.
- Listen to her.

342
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:00,200
You're a murderer.

343
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:04,070
When do you think you'd get out
and give us jobs at your hotel?

344
00:20:04,210 --> 00:20:06,240
When we're old and gray?

345
00:20:06,980 --> 00:20:08,810
Who does she think she is?

346
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:10,780
- Get the blanket.
- Okay.

347
00:20:10,850 --> 00:20:11,950
Go get it now.

348
00:20:12,350 --> 00:20:14,790
- She'll never learn.
- Don't! Stop it!

349
00:20:14,850 --> 00:20:17,250
Whatever. Stomp her.

350
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,960
Seriously. Learn your lesson!

351
00:20:19,020 --> 00:20:21,490
She needs a beating every day
just to get it through her head.

352
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:22,930
- Why won't you just get it?
- Seriously.

353
00:20:25,130 --> 00:20:26,760
- I'm home.
- Hey.

354
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:28,630
Where's Mom?

355
00:20:28,970 --> 00:20:31,570
She's trying to find out
what's going to happen with CEO Chae.

356
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,900
So you think CEO Chae will be released?

357
00:20:39,780 --> 00:20:40,840
Alright, Manager Kim.

358
00:20:41,180 --> 00:20:44,480
If you hear anything else, please call me.

359
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:47,420
Mom, what was that all about?
Why would CEO Chae be released?

360
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:49,850
I thought you said
she was going to stand trial.

361
00:20:50,450 --> 00:20:52,760
The real culprit turned themselves in.

362
00:20:52,890 --> 00:20:54,960
What? The real culprit came forward?

363
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,770
If I tell him everything now,

364
00:21:03,270 --> 00:21:05,140
will Grandfather be too shocked?

365
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,240
Should I wait a little longer?

366
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:11,170
But I want to go back
to being myself again.

367
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:14,610
Grandfather.

368
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:16,550
It's Seo Rin.

369
00:21:17,250 --> 00:21:18,280
Come in.

370
00:21:28,660 --> 00:21:32,900
Secretary Kim, you're here too.
I thought you were alone, Grandfather.

371
00:21:33,530 --> 00:21:37,500
Sit down. We were just talking
about your mother, actually.

372
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:39,900
My mother?

373
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:42,540
Don't you worry too much.

374
00:21:43,140 --> 00:21:45,180
Your grandfather will take care
of your mother...

375
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:48,480
Then there's no need for you
to intervene, Minister.

376
00:21:50,080 --> 00:21:52,120
I'll report that to the Chairman.

377
00:21:53,720 --> 00:21:55,750
Wait, what did he say?

378
00:21:57,220 --> 00:22:00,920
Congratulations.
CEO Chae is being released tomorrow.

379
00:22:01,990 --> 00:22:04,960
Did Minister Kim pull some strings?

380
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,160
No, that's not it.

381
00:22:06,160 --> 00:22:08,970
The real culprit
who murdered Oh Bok Gil turned himself in.

382
00:22:09,470 --> 00:22:12,400
What do you mean?
But my mom is the murderer.

383
00:22:12,700 --> 00:22:15,910
There's video evidence,
and they have Oh Bok Gil's phone.

384
00:22:16,170 --> 00:22:17,910
What do you mean,
the real culprit confessed?

385
00:22:20,910 --> 00:22:22,210
Hang on a second, Grandpa.

386
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:33,020
Baek Ho, they're saying
the real killer confessed.

387
00:22:33,090 --> 00:22:35,830
You heard too, Jang Mi?
I'm at the police station right now.

388
00:22:36,230 --> 00:22:37,890
I think you should come down here too.

389
00:22:38,100 --> 00:22:39,930
Okay, I'm on my way.

390
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,530
Come on.

391
00:22:44,370 --> 00:22:46,640
I'm telling you, I killed Oh Bok Gil.

392
00:22:46,870 --> 00:22:49,870
I'm here to confess, so what's the holdup?

393
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,780
Excuse me, Detective Kim.

394
00:22:54,410 --> 00:22:55,610
You...

395
00:22:56,110 --> 00:22:57,310
Ssangkal?

396
00:22:57,450 --> 00:22:59,850
- You punk, what are you doing?
- Hold him back.

397
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,250
You're the real killer?

398
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:03,850
Lawyer Kang, everyone is watching.
Please, calm down.

399
00:23:04,190 --> 00:23:06,760
It's not you. Why are you lying?

400
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:09,890
- You're not the one who killed my dad.
- Darn it.

401
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:10,960
You punk...

402
00:23:11,260 --> 00:23:12,300
Detective Kim.

403
00:23:12,900 --> 00:23:15,400
We just got a tip. Take a look at this.

404
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,730
- A tip?
- Yes.

405
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:21,940
Hold on.

406
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:43,490
Darn it.

407
00:23:43,960 --> 00:23:45,400
Watch where you're going!

408
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:48,000
- Are you trying to kill someone?
- I'm sorry.

409
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:54,940
I killed Oh Bok Gil. Got it?

410
00:23:55,170 --> 00:23:56,510
I killed him.

411
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:59,080
I'm also the one who bought the alcohol
from that supermarket.

412
00:23:59,380 --> 00:24:01,510
If you're going to commit perjury,
at least make it believable.

413
00:24:01,510 --> 00:24:03,550
How much did Chae Hwa Young pay you
to perjure yourself?

414
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:04,650
Darn it.

415
00:24:04,950 --> 00:24:07,950
Detective Kim, this man works
for Lee Kang Hyuk.

416
00:24:08,020 --> 00:24:09,320
They're all in it together.

417
00:24:09,590 --> 00:24:10,920
Chae Hwa Young...

418
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:13,790
is the one who killed my father
and framed Professor Kang Nam Bong!

419
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:14,860
Give me a break!

420
00:24:15,830 --> 00:24:18,260
I said I'm the killer!
What is with all this nonsense?

421
00:24:21,230 --> 00:24:24,670
Oh Bok Gil stalked and blackmailed me.
It was tough on me too.

422
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:27,440
When I saw him extorting money
from CEO Chae,

423
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:30,110
I just snapped and did it.

424
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:32,480
I was trying to take the money.

425
00:24:35,410 --> 00:24:38,320
- That's a solid motive, isn't it?
- Don't be ridiculous.

426
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,550
Did you cook up this story
with Manager Lee?

427
00:24:40,620 --> 00:24:41,920
Let go of me!

428
00:24:42,650 --> 00:24:43,790
Hey...

429
00:24:43,850 --> 00:24:45,790
Let go!

430
00:24:46,160 --> 00:24:47,560
Unbelievable.

431
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:52,030
(Yeongseo Detention Center)

432
00:25:14,380 --> 00:25:15,550
You've suffered too much.

433
00:25:33,970 --> 00:25:36,140
Let's get out of here
before the reporters show up.

434
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:38,940
Right.

435
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,800
What took you so long?

436
00:26:08,740 --> 00:26:11,040
Do you have any idea
how humiliated I was in there?

437
00:26:11,210 --> 00:26:12,880
I was trying to get Ssangkal
to turn himself in,

438
00:26:13,540 --> 00:26:16,010
but it looked like the Chairman
called the Minister.

439
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:20,150
So I was contemplating,
not sure what to do.

440
00:26:20,380 --> 00:26:22,190
You still don't understand Chairman Ma,
do you?

441
00:26:22,820 --> 00:26:24,650
It's not because he believes
I'm innocent, you know.

442
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:28,930
It's because he didn't want Seo Rin
to be the daughter of a murderer.

443
00:26:30,530 --> 00:26:34,430
If we had used the Minister's influence,
he would've tied my hands...

444
00:26:35,170 --> 00:26:38,670
and banned me from Dream Hotel for good,
that old geezer.

445
00:26:39,540 --> 00:26:41,500
Yes, I suppose you're right.

446
00:26:58,520 --> 00:27:00,490
When Chae Hwa Young gets out,
she's going to rip us apart.

447
00:27:00,790 --> 00:27:01,960
What am I going to do?

448
00:27:02,630 --> 00:27:04,290
I need to get on her good side
while I can.

449
00:27:04,730 --> 00:27:08,800
Ma'am, did you get the tofu
for when CEO Chae is released?

450
00:27:09,270 --> 00:27:10,870
Manager Lee probably already
took care of it.

451
00:27:10,930 --> 00:27:14,500
Seo Rin, are you not eating
because you're worried about your mom?

452
00:27:15,140 --> 00:27:17,570
Don't worry.
Manager Lee will bring her home.

453
00:27:19,140 --> 00:27:20,140
Okay.

454
00:27:22,910 --> 00:27:25,050
Hey, Manager Lee.

455
00:27:25,050 --> 00:27:26,220
What happened with CEO Chae?

456
00:27:26,680 --> 00:27:29,020
She went straight to the office
the moment she got out.

457
00:27:29,290 --> 00:27:32,360
- What?
- Her priority is to rebuild the company.

458
00:27:32,790 --> 00:27:33,790
Is that right?

459
00:27:35,190 --> 00:27:38,060
Your mother is
always so worried about the company.

460
00:27:38,800 --> 00:27:41,160
Well, there's a reason she's the CEO.

461
00:28:03,950 --> 00:28:05,960
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

462
00:28:10,230 --> 00:28:12,600
Welcome, Oh Jang Mi. You evil witch.

463
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:17,500
You knew it was me?

464
00:28:17,830 --> 00:28:18,840
Of course.

465
00:28:19,070 --> 00:28:21,770
Did you think I didn't know
you posed as Seo Rin and betrayed me?

466
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:25,480
Chae Hwa Young, it takes a lot of nerve
to crawl out here with that face.

467
00:28:26,140 --> 00:28:28,880
As if framing Professor Kang Nam Bong
for your crime wasn't enough,

468
00:28:28,950 --> 00:28:30,350
now you're pinning it on Ssangkal, too?

469
00:28:31,150 --> 00:28:33,780
Do you think you can keep
burying your crimes forever?

470
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:03,610
(The First Man)

471
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,280
Were you just using me this whole time?

472
00:29:05,980 --> 00:29:07,220
Please, just hear me out.

473
00:29:07,680 --> 00:29:10,420
I sincerely regret ever meeting you.

474
00:29:10,990 --> 00:29:13,020
Hong Ju, I'm ruined.

475
00:29:13,090 --> 00:29:14,290
You invested in crypto?

476
00:29:14,420 --> 00:29:16,030
I lost everything.

477
00:29:16,360 --> 00:29:18,530
I can't take this anymore! Seriously!

478
00:29:18,930 --> 00:29:20,660
Hello, CEO Chae.

479
00:29:20,700 --> 00:29:22,200
You know Mr. Noh Cheol Bong?

480
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,200
Ssangkal?

481
00:29:23,330 --> 00:29:25,870
I was told that if you didn't pay up,

482
00:29:25,870 --> 00:29:28,740
I should go find a woman named Oh Jang Mi.

483
00:29:28,840 --> 00:29:31,340
Ssangkal's girlfriend was here.
Find her, now.

484
00:29:31,710 --> 00:29:32,710
Oh Jang Mi?

485
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:35,850
He must have given you something
when he told you to find me.

486
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:37,080
What was it?

487
00:29:43,090 --> 00:29:45,090
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
